task.summary: Default task
Useless method removed from here
Update all the positions of the newly-reordered charts in the DB on drop, not on drag

Changed the signature of the addNewChart method to remove the boolean for checking if app is first launch, was being used to figure out whether to scroll the view if its the first launch, useless stuff. Second is the position variable belonging to each chart, was called order before.
Now implements Parcelable and also changed the order field to "position"

Get all the charts from the Nutrition API response and add them to the UI upon entry here. Also add them to the DB, and if the DB has already populated stuff, use them to populate the view on every other run, otherwise grab from API and load into the views.
Prevent items that are SECTIONS to be added as a meal. Setup the new SimpleSectioned List Adapter on the list of available meals. Set an Activity title in the toolbar properly.
If we're coming from Fitness, set the top bar to that background, otherwise set it to another background (Nutrition, Health, etc.)
Just changed the position of some code here

New adapter implementation for viewing the list of meals available for adding. This one implements a Pinned Section Header List View and differentiates between a SECTION viewtype and an ITEM viewtype, changes layouts accordingly. Pretty good stuff!

Add a different set of meals at the beginning of DB creation, this set includes Recently Added and All Items Section titles so that they may be separated within the AddNewMeal_Activity and showcase the sectioned listview in action
A lot of code moved around here only. Implemented the Update User Widgets code which triggers upon user re-ordering the widgets inside Customise Widgets and Charts activity
Added SectionType as a field to the MealItem class model
Update User Widgets API call implementation inside the API service
Add the No Action Bar Theme to the AddNewMealItem_Activity
Added the Toolbar as an include statement instead of having a fresh one, applies fitSystemWindows individually in this case also. XML addition fo the PinnedSectionListView
top layout here is given an id so that I can grab it from the Activity and change it according to which fragment we're coming from
Just code formatting here
Import statement for the new PinnedSectionListView
Add some snacks to the DB along with their section separators
Make the Add buttons under Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner and Snacks more sensitive to the touch
User Meals API response model and API call inside HTTP Service
No more need for annotations to get the ORM to recognize fields, DBConfigUtil takes care of that as a java program is run to initialize all the config for the DB
Fixed bug with setting a different background color at the top when entering this screen from Fitness or from Nutrition
RecyclerView adapter for displaying user meals in a recycler view under Breakfast, Lunch, etc.. inside Nutrition
Depending on where the user is adding a meal, add the meal to the database and then query the DB for the appropriate table, grab the meals for that section and populate the appropriate recyclerview
Give the top layout here an ID so that it can be used to set a background to that element
Change all the container views here into recyclerviews
Fix how this screen asks for permission to open the camera, set a toolbar and a toolbar title.
Several small UI edits after comments from demo
Updated to the latest version of MPAndroidChart library (probably will be dropping it completely soon)
Turn all number values in all the screens to int display, not double with 2 decimals
ItemTouchHelper and ItemTouchHelper Callback for RecyclerView implementation of swipe to delete, longclick to move around. Plus their corresponding implementation in code.
Just a minor change to the way the adapter for the recyclerviews works
Remove the 2 widgets that we don't have values for in the Fitness screen
Leave only the types of charts that we have values for in the Add New Chart screen
In the widgets adapter, also remove the widgets that were removed in the Fitness screen
Make all the charts return data for the last 7 entries (days), not all data
Shrink the height of the gridview inside the Fitness screen
Moved these two files into the Models package
References to the DB Helper file changed in 2 files after the move
New app icon added
Delete menu item added for the Slug Breakdown Activity (when you press on each chart)
Implementing delete chart functionality here. Remove all views and add them again after a delete happens, because this is not a listview, cannot notifydatasetchanged
New Application class implemented which includes initialization for the Crashlytics API (updated version reflected in gradle file)
Fix the actionbar size inside Add New Meal activity
Gridview height for Fitness and for Nutrition widgets fixed to certain sizes
Updated the Crashlytics API (Fabric) version
Entire Search For Meals implementation
